GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_StrategyOverview> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_StrategyOverview> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StrategyOverview> ;
    narr:childCount "29"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "5e21c6b4f121429eba397be728cabca110d64759" ;
    narr:narration """This hub tracks the evolution of aswritten.ai’s strategic positioning, centering on a [calibrated growth discipline](narr:Narrative_CalibratedGrowthDiscipline) that ties team sizing and pricing to validated demand rather than venture timelines. The tension between [venture-scale goals and calm-company execution](narr:Narrative_VentureScaleCalmCompanyExecution) remains central, managed through a [general vs. sellable](narr:Narrative_GeneralVsSellableTension) framing that treats the product as a general-purpose moat while using discovery-tooling as a sellable wedge. 

Go-to-market strategy has solidified around [beta-as-full-consulting](narr:Narrative_BetaAsConsulting), where the engagement itself serves as the primary mechanism for product validation. This is supported by [SMS-first acquisition](narr:Positioning_SMSProduct) as a low-friction entry point, with a clear [sequencing](narr:Sequencing_SMSProduct) from SMS-based interviews to a reusable [shared-backend marketplace](narr:Moat_SharedBackend). The [YC application](narr:Position_YC_Application_1) frames this as foundational infrastructure, while internal [design-by-rejection](narr:Narrative_DesignByRejection) continues to sharpen the boundaries between the product, org-development tooling, and the [user-facing vs. internal language](narr:Narrative_UserFacingVsInternalLanguageSplit) layers.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Decision_YCDemoBeats> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Moat_SharedBackend> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_BetaAsConsulting> ;
